sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / kubectl
    participant K8sAPI as K8s API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Admission Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Operator as Model Registry Operator<br/>controller-runtime
    participant K8s as K8s Resources<br/>(Deployment, Service, Route, RBAC)

    Note over User,K8s: Flow 1: Model Registry Instance Deployment
    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply ModelRegistry CR<br/>Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Validate/Mutate<br/>9443/TCP TLS (cert-manager)
    Webhook->>Webhook: MigrateOAuthProxy<br/>ToKubeRBACProxy()
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Admitted (mutated)
    K8sAPI-->>User: CR Created
    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch event<br/>443/TCP HTTPS SA Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Deployment<br/>(REST + kube-rbac-proxy sidecar)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Service<br/>(8443/TCP HTTPS)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Route<br/>(443/TCP reencrypt)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create PostgreSQL Deployment<br/>(if auto-provision)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create RBAC<br/>(Role, Binding, Group)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create NetworkPolicies
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Update CR Status

    Note over User,K8s: Flow 2: Model Registry REST API Access (kube-rbac-proxy)
    participant Client as API Client
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant KRBP as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant REST as Registry REST<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant DB as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP

    Client->>Router: POST /v1/model_registry<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    Router->>KRBP: Forward request<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS reencrypt<br/>Bearer Token forwarded
    KRBP->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS<br/>(can user GET service/{name}?)
    K8sAPI-->>KRBP: Allowed
    KRBP->>REST: Forward to localhost<br/>8080/TCP HTTP (loopback)
    REST->>DB: Query/Store metadata<br/>5432/TCP TCP<br/>Password auth, optional SSL
    DB-->>REST: Result
    REST-->>KRBP: JSON Response
    KRBP-->>Router: Response
    Router-->>Client: HTTPS Response

    Note over User,K8s: Flow 3: Model Catalog Access
    participant CatRouter as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant CatKRBP as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Catalog as Catalog Container<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant CatDB as Catalog PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP

    Client->>CatRouter: GET /api/catalog<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    CatRouter->>CatKRBP: Forward request<br/>8443/TCP reencrypt
    CatKRBP->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>(can user GET service/model-catalog?)
    K8sAPI-->>CatKRBP: Allowed
    CatKRBP->>Catalog: Forward to localhost<br/>8080/TCP HTTP (loopback)
    Catalog->>CatDB: Query catalog data<br/>5432/TCP TCP<br/>Password auth
    CatDB-->>Catalog: Result
    Catalog-->>CatKRBP: JSON Response
    CatKRBP-->>CatRouter: Response
    CatRouter-->>Client: HTTPS Response
